&gt; file

&gt; &gt; is or what has happened between the capture and the post. We listen

&gt; &gt; and think &quot;Wow! Great catch&quot; but we really do not know. 

&gt; &gt; 

&gt; &gt; Are you starting the scan on your 3 469&#39;s at different frequencies?

&gt; &gt; What is the ratio being mixed? Is it equal between the three? 

&gt; &gt; 

&gt; &gt; I believe that Mark and Debbie Constantino (sp)of Nevada use water

&gt; &gt; almost exclusively for their recordings. I have found that method to

&gt; &gt; be difficult in hearing the results. Are you feeling that those

&gt; &gt; communications are from spirits or earthbounds and what makes you 

&gt; feel

&gt; &gt; that way?

&gt; &gt; 

&gt; &gt; I&#39;ve recently started analyzing a 40 min 469 session. The results 

&gt; are

&gt; &gt; scary. I&#39;d say at this point, and I&#39;m only 1/2 way through, 90% of 

&gt; the

&gt; &gt; communication is negative in nature and mentions many supposed 

&gt; Demonic

&gt; &gt; names. The layers of voices are, in many cases, multiple. Often, the

&gt; &gt; listener hears very little of what is actually said. The voices can 

&gt; be

&gt; &gt; mocking or downright crude. I have not yet formed an opinion fully 

&gt; but

&gt; &gt; it would seem to me that these models are easy devices for lower 

&gt; level

&gt; &gt; entities to figure out how to use. I can not speak of the attitudes 

&gt; or

&gt; &gt; fears of those investigators present although at times, their voices

&gt; &gt; are a bit shaky. 

&gt; &gt; 

&gt; &gt; Babs

&gt; &gt; 

&gt; &gt; --- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups .com, Frank Ratka &lt;warrior18eii@ &gt; wrote:

&gt; &gt; &gt;

&gt; &gt; &gt; Very good observation Babs. Let me say that you have many friends

&gt; &gt; and associates here just for the simple fact that you have an 

&gt; interest

&gt; &gt; in ITC, are a researcher and a complex thinker. I think we have 

&gt; shown

&gt; &gt; in the past that we can have a disagreement and still remain 

&gt; friends.

&gt; &gt; You make a lot of good points in your post and I would like to know

&gt; &gt; who removes time from their recordings. I have never removed time 

&gt; from

&gt; &gt; my recordings and see no reason why anyone else would without saying

&gt; &gt; so in an accompanied post.

&gt; &gt; &gt; 

&gt; &gt; &gt; I have limited experience with the 12-469&#39;s as a single piece of

&gt; &gt; equipment. I have arranged mine per Mike&#39;s, &quot;Spiricomp&quot; design. I 

&gt; have

&gt; &gt; 3, 12-469&#39;s feeding a four channel mixer, which goes into a laptop

&gt; &gt; running DC6 with Soundsoap 2. Mine scan equally spaced on the FM 

&gt; band.

&gt; &gt; I have had pretty good results until recently.

&gt; &gt; &gt; 

&gt; &gt; &gt; At first the messages were pretty clear but I had a feeling I was

&gt; &gt; getting a different group than I normally have for the last few 

&gt; years.

&gt; &gt; When I would ask about my friends on the other side they would tell 

&gt; me

&gt; &gt; they will look for them. Well about 2 weeks ago the 12-469 

&gt; arrangement

&gt; &gt; started generating a lot of interference and feedback. I started

&gt; &gt; hearing radio static voices as I use to get with shortwave. Not 

&gt; voice

&gt; &gt; fragments but voices made of static (metallic and robotic). They 

&gt; were

&gt; &gt; breaking through the sweeping. I had a feeling someone else was 

&gt; trying

&gt; &gt; to force their way through. Finally the interference got so bad I 

&gt; was

&gt; &gt; forced to revert back to a simpler method I used before, which is

&gt; &gt; using fan noise. One of the first messages to come across was from a

&gt; &gt; familiar voice telling me and I quote, &quot;your method sucks&quot;. I have 

&gt; not

&gt; &gt; used the 12-469&#39;s since because of the clear messages I have been

&gt; &gt; getting using water and fan noise. That does not mean I have given 

&gt; up

&gt; &gt; &gt;  on the 12-469&#39;s but I won&#39;t use them again until I am persuaded 

&gt; to

&gt; &gt; by my friends on the otherside that they are willing to use and 

&gt; adapt

&gt; &gt; to it. To my knowledge only Misty, Laura and myself use water for

&gt; &gt; recording.

&gt; &gt; &gt; 

&gt; &gt; &gt; Regards,

&gt; &gt; &gt; 

&gt; &gt; &gt; Frank R.

