&gt; &gt; &gt; exactly what was done to the entire file. Time elapsed between &lt;br&gt;
&gt; words,&lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; what was amped, etc. I&#39;d also love to see some of these sessions &lt;br&gt;
&gt; video&lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; taped with the question asker facing the camera and a second hand&lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; clock visible. Truly, we aren&#39;t researching if we don&#39;t have some&lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; protocol in place.&lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; Here is an issue I have with the RS Hacks. I have the 469. It &lt;br&gt;
&gt; takes&lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; approximately 18 seconds to scan through the AM frequencies. Now, &lt;br&gt;
&gt; the&lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; typical person would think that we can take that 18 seconds and &lt;br&gt;
&gt; divide&lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; it by the number of AM stations to determine how long we are on &lt;br&gt;
&gt; each&lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; station before moving on to the next one. In that way we could&lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; determine what is impossible to be said via a radio fragment. &lt;br&gt;
&gt; However,&lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; that&#39;s not correct. The scan cycle can vary from one frequency to &lt;br&gt;
&gt; the&lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; next and of course the biggest problem is that some stations are&lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &lt;br&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; picked up over multiple frequencies; AM 640 can be heard on 630, &lt;br&gt;
&gt; 640,&lt;br&gt;
